```
The vector `(X 0, X 1, ... )` is a Gaussian vector.
The characteristic function of a Gaussian vector `Y` in `ŌäØ^d` is `exp(Ō¤©y, ╬╝Ō¤®_ŌäØ - ┬ĮŌ¤©y, ╬Ż yŌ¤®_ŌäØ)`.
In our case, `Y = (X 0, X 1, ... )`. The mean `╬╝` is `fun i Ōå” m_i` and the covariance `C` is `fun i j Ōå” Cov(X i, X j)`.
The characteristic function is `exp(Ōłæ L_i m_i - ┬Į Ōłæ L_i (Ōłæ C_{i,j} L_j) L_j)`.
Expanding: `exp(Ōłæ L_i m_i - ┬Į Ōłæ L_i L_j C_{i,j})`.
