The characteristic function of a tuple `(Y_1, Y_2, ..., Y_n)` of independent random variables is the product of their characteristic functions. So we need to show that the product of the characteristic functions of the components is equal to the characteristic function of a Gaussian distribution with the appropriate mean vector and covariance matrix.

